snippet.textDisplay:
8:08... my god I had something so similar happen to me as a kid. It was probably around 1993 or 1994. My family still had an original NES at home even though the SNES was out for a while. It was Christmas time and I remember asking my dad for the newer "Nintendo". I didn't really know that it was called a "Super Nintendo" since I was probably only 5 or 6 at the time. I just described it as the new "Nintendo" that you load the games in from the top and not from the front.
